net.sourceforge.waters.model.marshaller

Class ProductDESImporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.marshaller.ProductDESImporter

  • public class ProductDESImporter
extends Object

    A converter to translate the Product DES structure (ProductDESProxy) back into the Module (ModuleProxy) structure.

    This converter produces a very simple module without any structure or geometry information. It is intended for graphical display and editing of automata that have been automatically computed by analysis algorithms, or that have been imported from file formats that do not support structure or geometry information.

    It is possible to convert a full product DES object (ProductDESProxy) or individual automata (AutomatonProxy).

    Author:
    Robi Malik
    See Also:
    ModuleCompiler

      • importModule

        public ModuleProxy importModule(ProductDESProxy des)
                         throws ParseException
        Converts a product DES (ProductDESProxy) object to a module (ModuleProxy) object. If a default extension has been provided to the constructor, the file name of the created module will be constructed from its name and the default extension, and it will be located in the same directory as the original product DES.
        Parameters:
        des - The product DES to be imported.
        Returns:
        A module representing the same content as the given product DES. Compiling it should produce a result equal to des.
        Throws:
        ParseException
